'''''The Farlander Papers''''' is a companion book found only in the "Limited Edition" version of the [[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']] video game (the original floppy disk based release) written by [[Rusel DeMaria]].

The book contained a novella about [[Keyan Farlander/Legends|Keyan Farlander's]] assignment in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. In some points the narration breaks when Keyan opens a Rebel pamphlet which contained "[[A Call to Reason]]," spec sheets for the various spacecraft in the game, a "who's who" for the races and characters of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and much more. When he finishes reading, the narrative continues to Farlander's first mission. It serves as a scene-setter and provides helpful information for playing the game. The "Limited Edition" versions are identifiable only by a small round sticker on the front of the box.

Much of the story was later included and expanded as part of ''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]'', though it was largely rewritten and some parts of the story were left out in order to maintain ''The Farlander Papers'' status as a collector's item.<ref name="X-Wing Guide">''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]''</ref>

A similar book called ''[[The Stele Chronicles]]'' was released with the [[Star Wars: TIE Fighter (video game)|''Star Wars: TIE Fighter'']] video game.

